reason.tex:
\begin{align}
				  \dfrac{1}{x^2-1} = \dfrac{1}{(x-1)\cdot (x+1)} &= \dfrac{A}{x-1} + \dfrac{B}{x+1}\\
				  \implies 1 = A\cdot(x+1) &+ B\cdot(x-1) \\
				  = (A+B)\cdot x &+ (A-B) \\
				  \implies A+B = 0, A-B &= 1\\
				  \therefore A = \frac{1}{2}, B &= -\frac{1}{2}
				\end{align}
